OL,7,FHe said: "The Mineworkers' Pension
OL,8,FScheme, it's deferred wages, any
OL,9,Fpension is deferred wages, and that's
OL,10,Fto be recognised. The 50/50 split came
OL,11,Fin 1994, it was a crime. #4.4 billion
OL,12,Fplus syphoned off, trousered by the
OL,13,FTory Government."
OL,15,FConservative MP Paul Howell, who
OL,16,Frepresents Sedgefield, said a lack of
OL,17,Fconnectivity was letting down former
OL,18,Fmining villages, adding: "How can
OL,19,Fresidents aspire to social mobility,
OL,20,Fif they don't even have the physical
OL,21,Fmobility to reach better jobs.
