OL,7,FCommunities minister Lee Rowley said
OL,8,FLabour "does not own the story of
OL,9,Fmining in our country", adding:
OL,10,F"Labour do not get to disregard the
OL,11,Fsettled pension arrangements,
OL,12,Farrangements defended by the Labour
OL,13,Fparty for 13 years when they were on
OL,14,Fthis side of the House."
OL,16,FMr Rowley accepted "there is more to
OL,17,Fdo on levelling-up", adding: "We have
OL,18,Falways indicated that levelling up was
OL,19,Fa long term initiative which will take
OL,20,Ftime to work, but at least this
OL,21,FGovernment has made progress."
